description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and energetic full time person to join our busy Diagnostic Imaging Booking Team based at Hinchingbrooke Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of the hospital booking systems, PAS, Sunquest Ice and CRIS would be an advantage but if not training will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will require training in booking specialities and in particular the job provides a booking and telephone enquiry service to the patients for a variety of Diagnostic Imaging procedures. You will be joining a dedicated team of individuals providing a vital service to the Diagnostic Imaging Booking Team. You may also be required to cover reception duties within Imaging on an occasional basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The bookings will cover a variety of areas including CT, Nuclear Medicine, Fluoroscopy, MRI, Ultrasound and DEXA, the work is therefore varied and interesting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You need to be flexible, approachable, have good communication skills, with a polite telephone manner, and attention to detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contracted hours of work will be 37.5 hrs a week working Monday to Friday (flexible if needed to cover A/L and sickness) with some occasional weekend work. To be agreed between 8.00am to 8.00pm (at present time office hours are between 8am – 6pm)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
